The paper discusses clustering strategies that combine classical clustering algorithms and deep learning methods, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on deep autoencoder and spectral clustering, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV, followed by cs.NE and cs.CL.
